article.headline: Southern Miss tops Spring Hill 66-56
article.story: HATTIESBURG, Miss. -- Davon Hayes and Rasham Suarez both scored a career-high 16 points Saturday night and Southern Miss held off Division II Spring Hill 66-56. Matt Bingaya added 15 for the Golden Eagles (5-3), who trailed for much of the first half. Wesley Pietri scored 15 for the Badgers (1-7), who committed 21 fouls which the Golden Eagles converted to 17 of 26 free throws. Pietri hit back-to-back 3-pointers and the Badgers led 24-16, but Southern Miss ripped a 13-2 run in which Suarez sank three treys. Hayes made a free throw with 2 seconds to play and the Golden Eagles took a 29-28 halftime lead. Spring Hill rallied to a 45-42 second-half lead after a 3 by James Clarke, but Southern Miss retook the lead 48-47 on a dunk by Norville Carey. Sam Hutcheson pulled the Badgers to within two, 57-55, with a jumper, but Southern Miss sealed the win with nine free throws in the final 1:16.
